sentences: Chaya Arbel (Hebrew: חיה ארבל ; 1921 – 2007) was an Israeli composer.
Arbel studied piano and composition in Germany, until she immigrated to the British mandate of Palestine (1936), where she worked in agriculture at kibbutz HaMa'apil.
Only 25 years later, Arbel could resume her composition studies, with professor Leon Schidlowsky.
